          <protein>
            <id type="integer">160384</id>
            <name>P2X purinoceptor 2</name>
            <uniprot-id>Q9UBL9</uniprot-id>
            <description>
    ATP-gated nonselective transmembrane cation channel permeable to potassium, sodium and calcium (PubMed:10570044, PubMed:31636190). Activation by extracellular ATP induces a variety of cellular responses, such as excitatory postsynaptic responses in sensory neurons, neuromuscular junctions (NMJ) formation, hearing, perception of taste and peristalsis (By similarity). In the inner ear, regulates sound transduction and auditory neurotransmission, outer hair cell electromotility, inner ear gap junctions, and K(+) recycling (PubMed:23345450). Mediates synaptic transmission between neurons and from neurons to smooth muscle (By similarity).
  </description>
            <hmdbp-id nil="true"/>
            <gene-name>P2RX2</gene-name>
            <locus nil="true"/>
            <drugbank-id nil="true"/>
            <genbank-id nil="true"/>
            <species-id type="integer">1</species-id>
            <ec-numbers></ec-numbers>
            <synonyms nil="true"/>
            <element-states>
              <element-state>
                <id type="integer">292622</id>
                <biological-state-id type="integer">12621</biological-state-id>
              </element-state>
            </element-states>
          </protein>
          <protein>
            <id type="integer">160385</id>
            <name>P2X purinoceptor 3</name>
            <uniprot-id>P56373</uniprot-id>
            <description>
    Extracellular ATP-activated non-selective cation channel (PubMed:10440098, PubMed:27626375, PubMed:29674445, PubMed:31232692). Plays particularly important role in sensory neurons where its activation is critical for gustatory, nociceptive responses, visceral reflexes and sensory hypersensitization (By similarity).
  </description>
